<topic xml:id="openscap-profiles"
 role="reference" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>SSG Content, Directories, and Profiles</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="souvik.sarkar@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        Reference information on the &ssg; directory layout, the content available after
        installation, and the security profile supported for &slem;.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <section xml:id="openscap-profiles-directories">
    <title>SSG directories and files</title>
    <para>
      After installing the <package>scap-security-guide</package> package, the &ssg; security
      content is available in the following directories:
    </para>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><filename>/usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/</filename></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Contains the &ssg; security content in XML format. All files are named according to the
            SCAP component and the product they apply to. To list all available DataStream files,
            run:
          </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>ls -l /usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-*-ds.xml</command></screen>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><filename>/usr/share/doc/scap-security-guide/guides/</filename></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Contains human-readable HTML versions of the profiles. Each guide describes the rules
            included in a profile, the rationale behind each rule, severity levels, CCE
            identifiers, and available remediation options. To list all available guides, run:
          </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>ls -l /usr/share/doc/scap-security-guide/guides/ssg*.html</command></screen>
          <para>
            To view the guide for the <literal>general</literal> profile in a web browser, run:
          </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>firefox /usr/share/doc/scap-security-guide/guides/ssg-slmicro6-guide-general.html</command></screen>
          <para>
            The same content is also available online as static HTML pages at
            <link xlink:href="https://complianceascode.github.io/content-pages/guides/index.html"/>.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><filename>/usr/share/scap-security-guide/</filename></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Contains fix scripts for remediating vulnerabilities found during a scan, in the
            following formats:
          </para>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                Shell scripts: <filename>bash/*.sh</filename>
              </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                &ansible; playbooks: <filename>ansible/*.yml</filename>
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="openscap-profiles-supported">
    <title>Supported profile for &slem;</title>
    <para>
      The following security profile is supported by &suse; for &slem;. The profile is
      maintained in the
      <link xlink:href="https://github.com/ComplianceAsCode/content/tree/master/products/slmicro6/profiles">ComplianceAsCode</link>
      repository.
    </para>
    <table xml:id="openscap-profiles-supported-table">
      <title>Supported &ssg; profile for &slem;</title>
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colwidth="50*"/>
        <colspec colwidth="50*"/>
        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry>Profile name</entry>
            <entry>Profile ID</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry>General profile for &slem; (SLEM) 6</entry>
            <entry><literal>xccdf_org.ssgproject.content_profile_general</literal>
            </entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
    <para>
      To view the full list of profiles available in the DataStream file, including their IDs, run:
    </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>oscap info /usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-slmicro6-ds.xml</command></screen>
  </section>
</topic>
